casebody.data:
MARGARET M. GARRETT v. HAROLD B. GARRETT [No. 140,

October Term, 1945.]

Decided June 12, 1946.

The cause was argued before Marbury, C. J., Delaplaine, Collins, Grason, and Henderson. JJ.

Abram C. Joseph, with whom was Daniel C. Joseph on the brief, for the appellant. William Pepper Constable and John D. Alexander, with whom were Constable & Alexander on the brief, for the appellee. Grason, J.,

delivered the opinion of the Court.
